The paper deals with the analysis of a new random input model for bipartite matching, which involves the generation of random graphs and the study of the performance of a simple greedy algorithm. This falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Game Theory (cs.GT), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Information Theory (cs.IT), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). However, given the focus on graph theory and combinatorial optimization, cs.DM and cs.GT are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.DS and cs.IT, and then cs.SI.
